<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="451" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1476,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Remarks</emphasis>
. (1) Despite 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Ronkay, G. Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2017" box="[414,540,1477,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrocholorta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pacificorta">
<emphasis box="[414,540,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Pacificorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Ronkay, G. Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2017" box="[921,1071,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrocholorta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[921,1071,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Agrocholorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the fundamental differences in their valva and phallus structures suggest that this group of species should be considered as a distinct genus closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[267,365,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[267,365,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Ronkay, G. Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2017" box="[468,618,1548,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrocholorta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[468,618,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Agrocholorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (2) In the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Ronkay, G. Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2017" box="[1013,1139,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrocholorta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pacificorta">
<emphasis box="[1013,1139,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Pacificorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1156,1381,1548,1575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[1254,1312,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
), the authors did not designate a 
<typeStatus box="[461,509,1585,1611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">type</typeStatus>
species for the subgenus while, according to the Article 66.1 of 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[1235,1385,1585,1611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" refId="ref7544" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, The Natural History Museum, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, “an ichnotaxonomy at the genus-group level proposed after 1999 must have a 
<typeStatus box="[970,1018,1621,1647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">type</typeStatus>
species fixed for its name to be available”. Thus, the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Ronkay, G. Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2017" box="[403,529,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrocholorta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pacificorta">
<emphasis box="[403,529,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Pacificorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unavailable and a new genus is established herein instead of it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="451" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1476,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1692,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Species of the genus (
<figureCitation box="[576,708,1692,1719]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[200,1398,961,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-348@10.[151,1435,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Type species of Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 17, 19 and 20 in HNHM; 18 in CAV." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Figs 19, 20</figureCitation>
; also illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shikata, K." box="[928,1095,1692,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" pagination="150 - 164" refId="ref8006" refString="Shikata, K. (2015) Two new winter noctuid moths of the genus Conistra Hubner (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae) from the Ryukyu Chain, Japan. Tinea, 23 (3), 150 - 164." type="journal article" year="2015">Shikata (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1151,1394,1692,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[1246,1303,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">et al.</emphasis>
(2017))
</bibRefCitation>
are externally clearly different from other members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[761,859,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[761,859,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1179,1728,1755]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–8" captionStart-1="FIGURES 9–16" captionStart-2="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId-0="7.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-2="10.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox-0="[198,1393,183,1891]" captionTargetBox-1="[207,1414,182,1905]" captionTargetBox-2="[200,1398,961,1924]" captionTargetId-0="figure-26@7.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-18@8.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId-2="figure-348@10.[151,1435,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionTargetPageId-2="10" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–8. Marcinistra gen. n. and Baimistra gen. n. spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1 and 2 in HNHM; 3–6 in AFM; 7 and 8 in ZSM." captionText-1="FIGURES 9–16. Type species of subgenera of Conistra: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 9, 10 and 16 in HNHM; 11, 12 and 15 in BBT; 13 and 14 in GGF." captionText-2="FIGURES 17–20. Type species of Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 17, 19 and 20 in HNHM; 18 in CAV." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Figs 1–18</figureCitation>
) and more reminiscent of certain groups of the 
<taxonomicName box="[414,531,1764,1790]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[414,531,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Agrochola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout" authorityName="Prout" box="[788,976,1764,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leptologia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[788,909,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Leptologia</emphasis>
Prout
</taxonomicName>
(illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1143,1384,1764,1791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[1236,1291,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">et al.</emphasis>
(2017))
</bibRefCitation>
. The male genital capsule of 
<taxonomicName authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[422,542,1800,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Vargalorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[422,542,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Vargalorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[550,631,1801,1827]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[550,631,1801,1827]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[647,729,1800,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–29" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1389,216,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 27–29. Type species of Conistra (Dasycampa), Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 27 in BBT; 28 and 29 in HNHM." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) is most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1049,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1049,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1065,1195,1800,1827]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 24–26" captionStart-1="FIGURES 27–29" captionStartId-0="12.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-1="13.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1435,187,1901]" captionTargetBox-1="[155,1389,216,1902]" captionTargetId-0="figure-18@12.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-26@13.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="12" captionTargetPageId-1="13" captionText-0="FIGURES 24–26. Type species of subgenera of Conistra: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 24 and 26 in HNHM; 25 in BBT." captionText-1="FIGURES 27–29. Type species of Conistra (Dasycampa), Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 27 in BBT; 28 and 29 in HNHM." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Figs 24–27</figureCitation>
) and 
<emphasis box="[1259,1374,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Suginistra</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 27–29" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1389,216,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 27–29. Type species of Conistra (Dasycampa), Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 27 in BBT; 28 and 29 in HNHM." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) but differs in the pin-like apical process of the valva, a feature considered here as autapomorphic. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[285,405,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Vargalorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[285,405,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Vargalorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[412,491,1873,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,491,1873,1899]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[506,587,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–39" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[265,1323,186,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-26@15.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 36–39. Conistra, Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n. spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 36 and 39 in HNHM; 37 in BBT; 38 after Ronkay et al. (2017)." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) display no remarkable differences from 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1149,1873,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1149,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1164,1295,1872,1899]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 30–35" captionStart-1="FIGURES 36–39" captionStartId-0="14.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-1="15.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox-0="[166,1415,182,1902]" captionTargetBox-1="[265,1323,186,1902]" captionTargetId-0="figure-18@14.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-26@15.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="14" captionTargetPageId-1="15" captionText-0="FIGURES 30–35. Marcinistra gen. n., Baimistra gen. n. and Conistra spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 30 and 34 in HNHM; 31 in AFM; 32 and 33 in ZSM; 35 in BBT." captionText-1="FIGURES 36–39. Conistra, Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n. spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 36 and 39 in HNHM; 37 in BBT; 38 after Ronkay et al. (2017)." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Figs 34–37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="452" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1476,2042]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="452" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1908,1934]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,722,1908,1935]" pageId="9" pageNumber="451">External morphology of adults</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[738,871,1908,1935]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[200,1398,961,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-348@10.[151,1435,957,1951]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Type species of Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 17, 19 and 20 in HNHM; 18 in CAV." pageId="9" pageNumber="451">Figs 19, 20</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity box="[1085,1207,1908,1935]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18 mm</quantity>
in males and 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="19.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="18.0">18–20 mm</quantity>
in females. Antenna filiform in both sexes. Body and forewing ground colour varying from greyish-brown to reddish-brown. Forewing relatively broad, with pointed apex and straight outer margin. Pattern brown. Transverse lines thin, double. Subbasal line short, indistinct. Antemedial line sinuous. Medial line almost straight between cell and anal margin and angled inwards on Cu. Postmedial line slightly sinuous. Subterminal line interrupted into row of small spots. Terminal line sinuous. Orbicular and reniform stigmata large, latter one with dark spot posteriorly. Hindwing greyish-brown with paler proximal part and small and indistinct, semilunar discal spot. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[198,284,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–29" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[155,1389,216,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 27–29. Type species of Conistra (Dasycampa), Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 27 in BBT; 28 and 29 in HNHM." pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Uncus slender, elongate, down curved medially. Tegumen short, with broad, triangular and apically rounded penicular lobes. Vinculum more or less equal in length to tegumen, narrowly U-shaped. Valva narrow, gradually tapering distally. Costa with pin-like apical process directed distally and few tiny denticles on inner surface outwards from base of harpe. Clasper short, with thin, stick-like harpe somewhat dilated basally. Sacculus short but broad. Juxta large (in proportion to tegumen-vinculum complex), shield-like with tapered posterior half and posterior medial depression. Phallus relatively long and narrow, slightly tapered and down curved distally. Vesica narrow, tubular, recurved ventrally, with few semiglobular granulose medial diverticula and one robust thorn-like distal cornutus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[331,529,510,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[545,631,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–39" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[265,1323,186,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-26@15.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 36–39. Conistra, Suginistra and Vargalorta gen. n. spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 36 and 39 in HNHM; 37 in BBT; 38 after Ronkay et al. (2017)." pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor short, conical. Papillae anales trapezoid with rounded corners, setose. Apophyses thin, more or less equal in length, apophyses posteriores thinner than apophyses anteriores. Ostium broad. Antrum long, more or less champagne glass-shaped, dorso-ventrally flattened, heavily sclerotised, connected to ductus bursae with very short membranous ring. Ductus bursae tubular, narrow, heavily sclerotised. Corpus bursae pear-shaped, membranous, with four band-like signa of different lengths. Appendix bursae smaller than corpus bursae, sack-like, gelatinous with broad sclerotised areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1168,726,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="452" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,1168,726,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,726,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Distribution</emphasis>
. Species of the genus are known from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[885,949,727,753]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1003,1164,727,753]" name="Taiwan Island" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Taiwan Island</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="452" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,763,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name is an aggregation of the surname Varga and the genus group name 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1375,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Telorta</emphasis>
Warren
</taxonomicName>
and is dedicated to Prof. Zoltan Varga (
<collectingRegion box="[645,757,799,825]" country="Hungary" name="Debrecen" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Debrecen</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[769,871,799,825]" name="Hungary" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Hungary</collectingCountry>
), one of the authors of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Ronkay, G. Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2017" box="[1139,1265,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrocholorta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pacificorta">
<emphasis box="[1139,1265,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="452">Pacificorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
